The paper deals with a problem related to graph theory and wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The use of points in the plane and the study of the minimum number of nodes required to activate for communication also suggest computational geometry (cs.CG) as a likely sub-category. The problem of activating nodes for communication also suggests network optimization (cs.NE) and distributed systems (cs.DS) as possible sub-categories. The study of the complexity of the problem suggests game theory (cs.GT) and theoretical computer science (cs.SI) as other possible sub-categories.
